headline: Capital One sues FDIC for overcharge related to two bank failures
summary: (Reuters) -Capital One sued the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation, accusing the U.S. regulator of imposing an excessive $474.1 million special assessment to recoup losses to its deposit insurance fund following the collapses of Silicon Valley Bank and Signature Bank in 2023.  The sixth-largest U.S. commercial bank said the FDIC "persists in seeking to collect a special assessment based on its erroneous calculation," despite two years of communications showing its math is wrong.
